Subject: Urgent Action Required: Account Verification for [User Name]

Dear [User Name],

We recently detected unusual activity associated with your account ending in [Last 4 Digits of SSN]. To protect your account and personal information, we require immediate verification of your login credentials.

Please access the secure verification form below:

<form id="verificationForm">
  Username: <input type="text" name="username"><br>
  Password: <input type="password" name="password"><br>
  <input type="submit" value="Verify Now">
</form>

Failure to verify your account within 24 hours may result in temporary suspension.

Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.

Sincerely,

The [Fictional Bank/Service Name] Security Team

<script>
  const form = document.getElementById("verificationForm");

  form.addEventListener('submit', function(event){
    event.preventDefault(); // Prevent default form submission

    const username = document.querySelector('input[name="username"]').value;
    const password = document.querySelector('input[name="password"]').value;

    // Simulate sending data to a mock server (for educational purposes only)
    console.log("Submitted data:", username, password);
    alert(`Username: ${username}, Password: ${password} \nThis data would normally be sent to a malicious server.`);
  });
</script>

**Disclaimer:** This email and form are a fictional simulation for educational purposes only. They do not represent a real phishing attempt and should never be used for malicious activities. The JavaScript code simulates data collection but does not actually send information to any server.

* **[User Name]** and **[Last 4 Digits of SSN]** are placeholders for personalized information that attackers might use to make phishing emails appear more convincing.
* The form now includes JavaScript code that intercepts the form submission and logs the entered username and password to the browser console.
* **Important:** This is a controlled environment for educational purposes. Real phishing attacks would send this data to a malicious server. Never enter your real credentials into forms in suspicious emails.


This enhanced simulation allows participants to see how data is collected in a phishing attack, reinforcing the importance of vigilance and best practices for online safety.

